2026-02-28T23:33:38Z | sprint:SDLC-S0009 | performance | Sprint run with 5 template-only tasks took ~3 hours due to subagents running the full 858-test suite (uv run pytest tests/ -v, ~6 min each) multiple times per task during review gates. T00088 alone took 89 minutes (34 tool uses). For template-only changes (.md files) that have no unit tests, the full test suite is unnecessary overhead. Review gates should detect when changes are documentation/template-only and skip or limit test execution. Additionally, the subagent review gate spawns a sub-subagent reviewer that may also run tests, compounding the problem.
